... approves N35bn for NEPZA power station. The Federal Executive Council has approved the establishment of 20 new private universities, bringing to total 99 the number of private universities in Nigeria. Briefing State House Correspondent after the virtual FEC meeting presided by President Muhammadu Buhari today, Minister of Education, Mallam Adamu Adamu said the institutions will be given 3years provisional licenses by the National Universities Commission (NUC) to enable authorities monitor their quality.  Also speaking, Minister of Industry, Trade and Investment, Niyi Adebayo, said the Council approved the sum of N35 billion for the building of a power station by the Nigerian Export Processing Zone Authority (NEPZA), in Akamkpa, Cross River State. The Minister of Information and Culture, Alhaji Lai Mohammed on behalf of some colleagues, gave updates on contracts approved for the Ministry of Transportation and the Ministry of Aviation.  Our Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that Mines and Steel Development Minister, Olamilekan Adegbite, disclosed that FEC approved for the categorization of Aluminium Smelting Company of Nigeria in Ikot Abasi, Akwa Ibom State, as a power producing and strategic company, which will pave way for the production of aluminium will start in Nigeria.